21 peripherals and telephone, telegraph or telecommunications service
22 and equipment for use in a qualified aircraft maintenance or
23 manufacturing facility. For purposes of this paragraph, "qualified
24 aircraft maintenance or manufacturing facility" means a new or
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3661 Page 6

1 expa nding facility primarily engaged in aircraft repair, building or
2 rebuilding whether or not on a factory basis, whose total cost of
3 construction exceeds the sum of Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000.00)
4 and which employs at least two hundred fifty (250) new full-time-
5 equivalent employees, as certified by the Oklahoma Employment
